  <Placemark>
   <name>Tropical Storm Warning issued September 27 at 2:07PM EDT by NWS Miami FL</name>
   <styleUrl>#sev_severe</styleUrl>
   <Style>
    <BalloonStyle />
   </Style>
   <Snippet>* WHAT...North winds 20 to 30 kt with gusts up to 35 kt and seas
6 to 11 ft.

* WHERE...Coastal waters from Jupiter Inlet to Deerfield Beach
FL out 20 NM and Waters from Jupiter Inlet to Deerfield Beach
FL from 20 to 60 NM.

* WHEN...Saturday afternoon through Monday afternoon.

* IMPACTS...Tropical storm force winds and hazardous seas will
capsize or damage vessels and reduce visibility.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Tropical Depression Nine is forecast to
strengthen this weekend while moving northward through the
Bahamas. Tropical storm force winds will be possible across the
south Florida Atlantic waters Saturday afternoon through Monday
afternoon as the system strengthens to a Tropical Storm. Small
craft operators should take precautions to secure vessels.</Snippet>
