   </Style>
   <Snippet>At 1101 AM MST /1101 AM PDT/, local law enforcement reported
thunderstorms producing heavy rain across the warned area. Between 1
and 2 inches of rain have fallen. Flash flooding is already
occurring.

HAZARD...Life threatening flash flooding. Thunderstorms producing
flash flooding.

SOURCE...California Highway Patrol reported a vehicle underwater
at Araz Rd. and I-8.

IMPACT...Life threatening flash flooding of creeks and streams,
urban areas, highways, streets and underpasses.

Some locations that will experience flash flooding include...
Yuma, Winterhaven and Andrade.

This includes CA Interstate 8 between mile markers 90 and 96.</Snippet>
