   <name>Flood Advisory issued September 27 at 1:23PM EDT until September 27 at 4:30PM EDT by NWS Morristown TN</name>
   <styleUrl>#sev_minor</styleUrl>
   <Style>
    <BalloonStyle />
   </Style>
   <Snippet>* WHAT...Flooding caused by excessive rainfall is expected.

* WHERE...Portions of east Tennessee, including the following
counties, Hancock and Hawkins and southwest Virginia, including
the following county, Lee.

* WHEN...Until 430 PM EDT.

* IMPACTS...Minor flooding in low-lying and poor drainage areas.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...
- At 123 PM EDT, Doppler radar indicated heavy rain due to
thunderstorms. Minor flooding is ongoing or expected to begin
shortly in the advisory area. Between 1 and 2 inches of rain
have fallen.
- Additional rainfall amounts up to 0.5 inches are expected
over the area.
- Some locations that will experience flooding include...
Kyles Ford.
- http://www.weather.gov/safety/flood</Snippet>
