   <name>Marine Weather Statement issued September 27 at 2:01AM PDT by NWS Los Angeles/Oxnard CA</name>
   <styleUrl>#sev_minor</styleUrl>
   <Style>
    <BalloonStyle />
   </Style>
   <Snippet>Thunderstorms and showers are possible this afternoon and evening
across the inner coastal waters south of Point Conception
including the San Pedro Channel out to Santa Catalina Island, as
well as the outer waters south of Santa Cruz Island. Storms are
most likely near to the Los Angeles and Ventura County coasts.

Any thunderstorms will be capable of producing locally gusty
winds and rough seas, dangerous lightning, heavy rainfall with
reduced visibility and small hail.</Snippet>
